Follow all rules from this repository (tech-wise structure under `guides/`):

- `guides/frontend/angular/rules.md` — Angular/SPA baseline
- `guides/frontend/angular/core-angular-skill.md` — deep `@rcubinity/core-angular` skill
- `guides/backend/nestjs/rules.md` — NestJS backend baseline + shared `core/`
- `guides/backend/nestjs/core-nestjs-skill.md` — deep shared `core/*` NestJS skill
- `guides/backend/python/rules.md` — Python services and workers
- `guides/design/ui-ux-styling-bootstrap/ui.md` — UI guidelines
- `guides/design/ui-ux-styling-bootstrap/ux.md` — UX guidelines
- `guides/design/ui-ux-styling-bootstrap/styling.md` — styling guidelines
- `guides/design/ui-ux-styling-bootstrap/bootstrap.md` — Bootstrap usage guidelines
- `guides/platform/devops.md` — delivery and infra hygiene
- `guides/platform/security.md` — security baseline
- `guides/platform/testing.md` — testing expectations
- `guides/platform/review-checklist.md` — PR review checklist
- `guides/docs/context-and-docs.md` — atlas/capsule documentation conventions
- `guides/docs/capsule.md` — capsule update workflow

These rules are **generic** and **multi-project**. Repository-specific rules in each app’s `.cursor/rules/` or local docs **override** when they conflict.

Always aim for production-quality, maintainable code that matches the **existing** patterns in the target repository.
